[Patient] Can you tell me how much fluid I should be drinking each day?
[Healthcare Educator] Aim for about 6-8 cups of fluid daily, including water, juice, and soups.
[Patient] Should I limit my fluid intake if I have heart failure?
[Healthcare Educator] Yes, limiting fluids can help prevent fluid build-up in your body and manage symptoms.
[Patient] Can I still drink my favorite teas and sodas?
[Healthcare Educator] It's best to limit drinks with caffeine and sugar, as they can affect your heart.
[Patient] How can I track my fluid intake throughout the day?
[Healthcare Educator] Try using a water bottle or journal to keep track of how much you drink.